cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.CY, cs.AI 

The paper discusses the use of text mining techniques and computational capacity to extract semantic information from medical publications, which falls under the sub-categories of natural language processing (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and databases (cs.DB). The use of Wikipedia as a source of accessible textual information also involves the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The mention of limitations in the access to data and lack of structure suggests the sub-category of cybersecurity (cs.CY) as a possible area of concern.
